main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted in the sky over La Camp, Louisiana, on April 6, 1960. The object was observed as a luminous object moving rapidly through the sky before disappearing.
interesting points: The report includes detailed measurements of distances from various points of impact related to the incident., Several photographs document the initial impact area and markings on the terrain., The first point of impact was logged with specific distances noted for subsequent points., Paint samples were collected from one of the impact sites., The report was investigated by personnel from Barksdale Air Force Base.
sighted object: luminous object moving rapidly through the sky
witness description: Reported by Mr. Cleo Joseph LaCamp
